{
  "stem": "22174.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They [? have ?] Jewish cousins.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- they all wrote about my mother, what happened to her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they wrote that, as long as she was in Stendel, she was taken care of by friends.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, after the war, I got a-- got a very densely written postcard from another non-Jewish woman that was a friend of our family.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she wrote the same thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so I got-- I got four [INAUDIBLE] postcards.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one of them, my mother writes that my sister was trying to get a visa for her for some small country, to buy a visa, you know, you had to buy these visas.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the-- so on one of those postcards my mother writes a-- a-- a visa for Cuba is pending.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- and then the war broke out, and no more ships [INAUDIBLE] Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Eventually, the [INAUDIBLE], the visa came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And one postcard is where she writes that my father had died, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and the other postcard-- the third postcard-- is where she writes that the change of address is imminent.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was the last postcard, which I got in El-Alamein.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it's from Warsaw, from the ghetto, where she writes even the address, in the [? hall. ?] And--",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in '42.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the last what I-- what I heard of-- from her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And always she writes how she longs for us, for my sister and for me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she always hoped that we would see each other again, except in the one letter, in one postcard before the deportation, where she wrote that she expects a change in address.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
